Bull Bull is a kind of traditional card game of poker and popular in Guangdong, Guangxi, Hunan and the Jiangsu and Zhejiang provinces. The greatest feature of Bull Bull is the rules are easy to understand

The game uses 52 cards (without Joker). 
Deal 5 cards to each player in every game round. 
Find 3 cards which can add up to 10 or a multiple of 10. 
If the rest of 2 cards add up to over 10, the total has to be minus 10, then, the remaining points compare the points with Banker.

During the game, if the points are the same, players need to choose the highest ranking card from the 5 cards to compare. The player who has the highest ranking card wins. If the points and rank are the same, players need to compare the suit. Please see the table below.

Bull 6（including Bull 6）and less are normal card type
J，Q，K are equal to 10, other cards shall carry their denoted numerical value. Ace equal 1.
Calculation methods of “bet on Many” payoff: card type odds of Player1/Player2/Player3 subtract card type odds of Banker; if the card type of player and banker is same, payoff follows odds on equal.

Examples:
1. Bet on ‘Many’ under Player2, Player2 result is ‘Bull 9’, Banker result is ‘Bull 2’. Player2 Bull 9(8.55times) – Banker Bull 2(1.9 times)=6.65 times, player2 win: bet amount *6.65.

2. Bet on ‘Many’ under Player2, Player2 result is ‘No Bull’, Banker result is ‘Bull 5’. Player2 No Bull(0times) – Banker Bull 5(5 times)= -5 times, player2 lose: bet amount *5.

3. Bet on ‘Many’ under Player2, Player2 result is ‘Bull 9’, Banker result is ‘Bull 9’. The biggest card ofBanker is bigger than the biggest card of Player2, Banker win. Player2 lose bet amount*1.
